f10Modules.name: f10Modules
f10Modules.description: f10Modules provides a root object identifier from which MODULE-IDENTITY values may be based.

f10Experiment.name: f10Experiment
f10Experiment.description: f10Experiment provides a root object identifier from which experimental mibs may be temporarily based. mibs are typicially based here if they fall in one of two categories 1) are IETF work-in-process mibs which have not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the IANA. 2) are force10 work-in-process which has not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the force10 assigned number authority, typicially because the mib is not ready for deployment. NOTE WELL: support for mibs in the f10Experiment subtree will be deleted when a permanent object identifier assignment is made.
